Here are the **best free website builders (2026)**—ranked by ease of use, features, and what they’re best for.

---

# 🏆 Best free website builders

### 1. **Wix** (Best overall)

* Drag-and-drop builder with tons of freedom
* 800+ templates + AI site generator
* Free plan includes hosting (with ads)
* Great for: beginners, small businesses, portfolios

👉 Widely ranked #1 because of flexibility and features ([TechRadar][1])

---

### 2. **Square Online** (Best for selling)

* One of the only **free ecommerce builders**
* Built-in payments and product listings
* Great for: small online stores

👉 Stands out since most free builders don’t allow selling ([TechRadar][1])

---

### 3. **WordPress.com** (Best for blogs & flexibility)

* Massive plugin ecosystem (on paid plans)
* Strong blogging + SEO tools
* Free plan includes basic site + subdomain

👉 Best if you want long-term scalability

---

### 4. **Webflow** (Best for advanced design)

* Visual builder with near “code-level” control
* Great animations and custom layouts
* Free plan available (limited publishing)

👉 Ideal for designers and developers ([Cybernews][2])

---

### 5. **Weebly** (Easiest for beginners)

* Very simple drag-and-drop editor
* Includes basic ecommerce (up to ~10 products)
* Free plan with branding

👉 Good if you want something super easy ([SPUNK.CODES][3])

---

### 6. **HubSpot CMS Hub** (Best for business tools)

* Free plan with CRM + marketing tools
* Connects to business workflows
* Great for: startups & lead generation

---

### 7. **SITE123** (Fastest setup)

* Guided setup (almost automatic)
* Limited customization but very quick

---

